<div id="node-236" class="node odd teaser node-type-posubpage">
  
    <h2 class="title"><a href="/program-overview/what-is-icshp" title="What is the ICS Honors Program?">What is the ICS Honors Program?</a></h2>
  
  <div class="meta">
      </div>
  
    
  <div class="content">
    <div class="content">
<p><a href="/program-overview/what-is-icshp"><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2642/4110834226_b6f1103343.jpg" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p>The ICS Honors Program (ICSHP) provides an opportunity for students in any of the Bren School's majors to carry out a research project under the direction of a Bren School faculty member.</p>
</div>  </div>
  
  
  </div>
<!-- /#node-236 -->          </td>
                  <td class="col-2 col-last">
            
<!-- start node.tpl.php -->
<div id="node-203" class="node even teaser node-type-posubpage">
  
    <h2 class="title"><a href="/program-overview/step-1" title="Step 1: Course Requirements">Step 1: Course Requirements</a></h2>
  
  <div class="meta">
      </div>
  
    
  <div class="content">
    <p><a href="/program-overview/step-1"><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5190/5644041977_ee39974236.jpg" title="test" height="334" width="500" /></a></p>
<p>Students joining the program participate in the Bren School Honors Seminar (ICS H197), which provides an introduction to research areas in the school. ICS H197 is graded Pass/Not Pass, and the principal formal requirement is that you attend and participate. Students who are in the ICSHP are required to enroll in ICS H197 in the fall of their first year in the ICSHP.</p>  </div>
  
    <div class="links">
