<div id="node-204" class="node odd teaser node-type-posubpage">
  
    <h2 class="title"><a href="/program-overview/step-2" title="Step 2: Honors Seminar (ICS H197)">Step 2: Honors Seminar (ICS H197)</a></h2>
  
  <div class="meta">
      </div>
  
    
  <div class="content">
    <p><a href="/program-overview/step-2"><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5267/5599451278_a6f7eb202d.jpg" height="333" width="500" /></a></p>
<p>ICS H197 provides an opportunity for the Bren School's undergraduate honors students to learn about the research taking place in the school and to begin to get involvedÂ with this research. The main purpose of this course is to help you learn what sort of research is being conducted, which people do what, and how to get connected with a research project.</p>
<p>Several types of meetings are planned for this seminar, including the following:</p>  </div>
  
