<div id="node-207" class="node even teaser node-type-posubpage">
  
    <h2 class="title"><a href="/program-overview/step-3" title="Step 3: Finding a Faculty Advisor and Taking CS H198">Step 3: Finding a Faculty Advisor and Taking CS H198</a></h2>
  
  <div class="meta">
      </div>
  
    
  <div class="content">
    <p><a href="/program-overview/step-3"><img src="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~sao/ICSHPsite/program_overview_step_3.jpg" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>To complete the honors program, you must take two quarters of independent, supervised work (CS H198 or In4matx H198) with your faculty advisor. (In some cases, your advisor might ask you to take a graduate course to substitute for the first quarter.)</p>  </div>
  
    <div class="links">
